Compulsive overeating.
 Compulsive overeating is a behavior used in an attempt to numb or nurture feelings that are threatening to the person.
 Emotional states are soothed by use of food.
 Treatment is designed to respond to internal, biologic causes of hunger and satiety while simultaneously allowing feelings to surface and be dealt with.
 Work on the inner child enables the person to identify and deal with unmet needs and correct distortions from childhood.
 The secondary gain realized from the extra weight is examined, and direct means of dealing with these needs explored.
 The focus of recovery is on learning to nurture the self, physically and emotionally.
